
Basic Level Commands

  Navigation & File System
    pwd - Print working directory
    ls - List directory contents (ls -la for detailed view)
    cd - Change directory
    mkdir - Make directories
    rmdir - Remove empty directories
    touch - Create empty files or update timestamps
    rm - Remove files (rm -r for directories)
    cp - Copy files and directories
    mv - Move or rename files
    cat - Display file contents
    less - View file contents page by page
    more - Similar to less
    head - Display first lines of a file
    tail - Display last lines of a file


  File Information  
    file - Determine file type
    stat - Display file statistics
    wc - Word, line, and byte count

  Basic System Info
    whoami - Display current user
    date - Show system date and time
    cal - Display calendar
    clear - Clear terminal screen
    history - Show command history
    echo - Display text or variables



Intermediate Level Commands

  File Searching & Processing
    find - Search for files in directories
    locate - Find files by name (uses database)
    grep - Search text patterns in files
    egrep - Extended grep with regex
    sed - Stream editor for text manipulation
    awk - Pattern scanning and processing
    cut - Remove sections from lines
    sort - Sort lines of text
    uniq - Report or omit repeated lines
    diff - Compare files line by line
    comm - Compare sorted files

  File Permissions & Ownership
    chmod - Change file permissions
    chown - Change file owner
    chgrp - Change group ownership
    umask - Set default permissions

  Archives & Compression
    tar - Archive files
    gzip - Compress files
    gunzip - Decompress gzip files
    bzip2 - Compress with bzip2
    zip - Package and compress files
    unzip - Extract zip archives

  Process Management
    ps - Display process status
    top - Real-time process monitoring
    htop - Interactive process viewer
    kill - Terminate processes
    killall - Kill processes by name
    bg - Send job to background
    fg - Bring job to foreground
    jobs - List background jobs
    nohup - Run command immune to hangups

  Disk Usage
    df - Display disk space usage
    du - Estimate file space usage
    mount - Mount filesystems
    umount - Unmount filesystems

  Networking Basics
    ping - Test network connectivity
    ifconfig - Configure network interfaces (older)
    ip - Show/manipulate routing and devices
    netstat - Network statistics
    wget - Download files from web
    curl - Transfer data from URLs

  User Management
    useradd - Add new user
    userdel - Delete user
    usermod - Modify user account
    passwd - Change user password
    su - Switch user
    sudo - Execute command as superuser



Advanced Level Commands

  System Administration
    systemctl - Control systemd services
    service - Run System V init scripts
    journalctl - Query systemd logs
    dmesg - Display kernel ring buffer messages
    lsof - List open files
    fuser - Identify processes using files
    strace - Trace system calls
    ltrace - Trace library calls
    cron - Schedule periodic tasks
    at - Schedule one-time tasks
    anacron - Run commands periodically


  Advanced Networking
    ss - Socket statistics (modern netstat)
    nmap - Network exploration and security scanner
    tcpdump - Packet analyzer
    iptables - Configure firewall rules
    nft - Nftables firewall configuration
    ssh - Secure shell remote login
    scp - Secure copy over SSH
    rsync - Remote file synchronization
    nc (netcat) - Network utility for reading/writing network connections
    traceroute - Trace packet route to host
    dig - DNS lookup utility
    nslookup - Query DNS servers
    host - DNS lookup

  Disk & Filesystem Management
    fdisk - Partition table manipulator
    parted - Partition manipulation program
    mkfs - Create filesystem
    fsck - Filesystem consistency check
    lsblk - List block devices
    blkid - Locate block device attributes
    dd - Convert and copy files (disk imaging)
    mdadm - Manage RAID arrays
    lvm - Logical Volume Manager


  Performance & Monitoring
    vmstat - Virtual memory statistics
    iostat - CPU and I/O statistics
    sar - System activity reporter
    mpstat - Multiprocessor statistics
    iotop - I/O monitoring per process
    perf - Performance analysis tool
    sysctl - Configure kernel parameters

  Advanced Text Processing
    tr - Translate or delete characters
    tee - Read from stdin and write to stdout and files
    xargs - Build and execute commands from input
    parallel - Execute jobs in parallel
    jq - JSON processor
    xmllint - XML parser and validator
    column - Format output into columns

  Package Managemen
    Debian/Ubuntu: apt, apt-get, dpkg, aptitude
    RedHat/CentOS: yum, dnf, rpm
    Arch: pacman
    snap - Install snap packages
    flatpak - Install flatpak applications

  Security & Encryption
    gpg - GNU Privacy Guard encryption
    openssl - SSL/TLS toolkit
    ssh-keygen - Generate SSH keys
    iptables-save/restore - Save/restore firewall rules
    fail2ban - Intrusion prevention
    selinux - Security-Enhanced Linux commands
    apparmor - Application security framework

  Advanced Shell Features
    alias - Create command shortcuts
    source or . - Execute commands from file
    export - Set environment variables
    env - Display environment variables
    exec - Replace shell with command
    eval - Evaluate arguments as command
    trap - Catch signals in scripts

  Specialized Tools
    screen - Terminal multiplexer
    tmux - Modern terminal multiplexer
    vim/nano/emacs - Text editors
    git - Version control system
    make - Build automation tool
    gcc/g++ - Compilers
    gdb - GNU debugger
    valgrind - Memory debugging and profiling
    docker - Container management
    kubectl - Kubernetes cluster management





  

  








  
